The Seam Project is the vision of a multi-disciplinary cohort of artists seeking to connect their work to the communities they live in, give to, and thrive from.

The Seam Project consists of four shows in four months, one show for each month, with each show showcasing the work of four to eight artists and their collaborators on a 4x4 stage in the yard of a house.

Each house has been selected by the region of Austin in which it sits, (South, North, West, and East) and each show's mission is to bring performances directly to the people who live in the corresponding neighborhoods of these homes to foster a greater sense of community.

