The goal set for this fundraiser reflects The Seam Project's belief in paying it's artists for their work and creating a comprehensively memorable experience for the audience.

The money raised from this campaign will go directly to the stipend of the contributing artists and amenities for patrons such as drinks, comfortable seating, and quality facilities.

Any funds raised beyond our set goal will go immediately to the next project in this cycle, North, set to open in October.

The ultimate goal of The Seam Project is not only to bring performances to communities, but to generate and cultivate work by the people in the community to better understand their experience as a citizen of Austin and their neighborhood. This next phase of The Seam Project will begin in the second year of production.

